description: For sale: $168,900. This charming 2 Bedroom 2 Bath Home has been completely updated.  Taken down to the studs and completely rewired, new plumbing, new insulation & sheetrock. You'll love the warm in floor heat on the main floor and the cozy 4 Season Porch with gas fireplace and bay window.  Kitchen with Bar and dining area are open to Living Room with red elm hardwood floors. Hall Pantry. Gas Range in Kitchen is Negotiable.  Main floor bedroom & beautiful tile shower in 3/4 bath. Main floor den with bay window could also be another bedroom.  Lower level has large family room that walks out to patio.  2nd bedroom and full bath.  Updated mechanicals - gas boiler (back up) electric boiler connects to main floor  in floor heat, off peak electric panel, 2 Heat & Cooling pumps, water softener and filtration system.  Partially fenced yard.  Space for gardens and Large Shed.

For sale: $785,000. What an opportunity! Amazing home on 3.85 acres with 320' overlooking Lake Pepin and MS River. This property features privacy, huge trees and breathtaking views that make every season stunning. This gorgeous home was thoughtfully designed with loads of upgrades in every interior space. Home just freshly repainted in neutral colors and all popcorn ceilings removed. Meticulous sellers have gutted kitchen, upgraded flooring, replaced windows, rebuilt extra art studio building, replaced siding, roofs, added gutters, re-designed floor plan, new septic pump, AC...the list is long!  Relax and unwind with nature and beauty both inside and out this lovely home.

description: For sale: $580,000. Your lake cabin is waiting!    A great mix of old and new with a few places remaining to make it your own.  This waterfront is amazing.  Bring the jet skiis, kayaks, paddle boards, boats or canoes.  Entertain, relax and enjoy the updated kitchen and main floor bath. Main floor master has a big walk in closet and opens up to the lakeside deck.  The kitchen / living room area has expansive views of the Lake and overlooks a huge yard.  Bedroom 2 is downstairs along with another bathroom, laundry room and family room that walks out towards the lake.  Great outdoor spaces include a "cook shack" fire pit and wooden beach platform.  Bring your gang and enjoy this scenic, serene property now and for generations to come.

description: Recently sold: $167,000. First floor has dining , living room and bedroom with hardwood floors.  New kitchen.  Two bedrooms and bathroom in basement.  The inside was painted in 2011, outside in 2019.  It has a new roof (2013) and new septic system (2009).The large front yard is across the road from Frontenac State Park, and the even larger back yard is up the hill from the town park.  Frontenac is a beautiful, quiet, sleepy historic town surrounded on three sides (in an arc) by the state park and on the fourth by Lake Pepin.

description: Recently sold: $159,900. Lovely Greek Revival cottage style home with a unique history. Original part of the house was built in 1860 with a 1.5 story addition in 2002. Great blend of old and new! Main floor features rustic original hardwood floors, large dining room with wood-burning fireplace, kitchen with custom cabinetry and center island, pantry, office/library, family room with gas fire place, formal living room, powder room and laundry room. Second floor has hardwood floors, three large bedrooms with walk-in closets, and two bathrooms. Master bedroom has full bathroom and a balcony overlooking the back yard. This is a perfect family home or second home! Fresh paint on the exterior and many rooms throughout! Two-stall attached garage. Three blocks to Lake Pepin boat launch and beach. One mile to State Park with great hiking and camping.

Recently sold: $63,636. Country setting in New Town Frontenac. Home is on .6 acres. 2bedroom home that is in move-in condition with front area sunroom. Large 2 stall garage and storage shed with a large window that could upgrade to a heated workshop.

description: Recently sold: $470,000. Lake front home located in Frontenac on Lake Pepin.  Has 3 full bedrooms and a room with a Murphy bed and that functions as a 4th bedroom along with a spacious 3 car garage with substantial storage.  Reclaimed wood is used throughout the home.  Reclaimed wood seamlessly blends with  materials such as maple cabinets, fireslate counter tops, and built in cabinetry throughout.  Spacious mudroom.  Comfortably sleeps 10 and has a wide open feel with long sight lines.  Renovated in 2013 and has many modern amenities -- gas stovetop, 3-sided fireplace, heated floor in master bath, wifi enabled, among others. Is part of a well kept association that has access to Lake Pepin and a boat slip on the association doc.   The home backs up to the bluffs of Frontenac State Park with over 4,000 acres that include 17 miles of hiking trails, fantastic views of Lake Pepin and the Wisconsin bluffs.
